876  f = first_living_edge_graph(g, ref_nodev(g->nodes, t->node), t->dir, &info);
877  if(info != WT_TRACE_MSG_ONE){ if(msg) *msg = info; break; }
878  e = g->edges->buffer + f->idx;
879  n = ref_nodev(g->nodes, f->flg? e->node1 : e->node2);
880  dir = f->flg? !e->dir1 : e->dir2;
881  t->node = n - g->nodes->buffer;
882  t->dir = dir;
883  f = first_living_edge_graph(g, n, !dir, &info);
884  if(info != WT_TRACE_MSG_ONE){ if(msg) *msg = -1 - info; break; }
885  step ++;
886  }
887  return step;
888 }

◆ detach_repetitive_frg_core_graph()

static u4i detach_repetitive_frg_core_graph ( Graph *  g,
u8i  nid,
u4i  max_dist,
u8i  visit,
u8v *  nds,
u8v *  heap 
)
inlinestatic
1784  {
1785  frg_t *n, *w, *x;
1786  edge_ref_t *f;
1787  lnk_t *e;
1788  u8i idx, wid, xid, eid;
1789  u4i k, i, j, bidx, bcnt[2];
1790  int off;
1791  n = ref_frgv(g->frgs, nid);
1792  n->bt_visit = visit;
1793  clear_u8v(nds);
1794  clear_u8v(heap);
1795  for(k=0;k<2;k++){
1796  bcnt[k] = 0;
1797  idx = n->lnks[k].idx;
1798  while(idx){
1799  f = ref_edgerefv(g->lrefs, idx);
1800  e = ref_lnkv(g->lnks, f->idx);
1801  idx = f->next;
1802  if(e->closed) continue;
1803  wid = f->flg? e->frg1 : e->frg2;
1804  w = ref_frgv(g->frgs, wid);
1805  if(w->bt_visit == visit){
1806  // TODO: remove the fprintf after debug
1807  fprintf(stderr, " -- F%llu:%c -> F%llu:%c already visited in %s -- %s:%d --\n", nid, "+-"[k], wid, "+-"[w->rep_dir], __FUNCTION__, __FILE__, __LINE__); fflush(stderr);
1808  return 0;
1809  }
1810  push_u8v(nds, wid);
1811  w->bt_visit = visit;
1812  w->rep_dir = f->flg? !e->dir1 : e->dir2;
1813  w->bt_idx = (bcnt[k] << 1) | k;
1814  bcnt[k] ++;
1815  off = n->len / 2 + e->off;
1816  if(off < 0) off = 0;
1817  w->rep_idx = off + w->len; // rep_idx is used as dist
1818  if(w->rep_idx < max_dist){
1819  array_heap_push(heap->buffer, heap->size, heap->cap, u8i, wid, num_cmp(g->frgs->buffer[a].rep_idx, g->frgs->buffer[b].rep_idx));
1820  }
1821  }
1822  }
1823  if(bcnt[0] == 0 || bcnt[1] == 0) return 0;
1824  if(bcnt[0] < 2 && bcnt[1] < 2) return 0;
1825  // extending branches to max_dist in length
1826  while(heap->size){
1827  wid = heap->buffer[0];
1828  array_heap_remove(heap->buffer, heap->size, heap->cap, u8i, 0, num_cmp(g->frgs->buffer[a].rep_idx, g->frgs->buffer[b].rep_idx));
1829  w = ref_frgv(g->frgs, wid);
1830  idx = w->lnks[w->rep_dir].idx;
1831  while(idx){
1832  f = ref_edgerefv(g->lrefs, idx);
1833  e = ref_lnkv(g->lnks, f->idx);
1834  idx = f->next;
1835  if(e->closed) continue;
1836  xid = f->flg? e->frg1 : e->frg2;
1837  x = ref_frgv(g->frgs, xid);
1838  if(x->bt_visit == visit) continue;
1839  off = w->rep_idx + e->off;
1840  if(off < 0) off = 0;
1841  if(off > (int)max_dist) continue;
1842  push_u8v(nds, xid);
1843  x->bt_visit = visit;
1844  x->rep_dir = f->flg? !e->dir1 : e->dir2;
1845  x->bt_idx = w->bt_idx;
1846  x->rep_idx = off + x->len;
1847  if(x->rep_idx < max_dist){
1848  array_heap_push(heap->buffer, heap->size, heap->cap, u8i, xid, num_cmp(g->frgs->buffer[a].rep_idx, g->frgs->buffer[b].rep_idx));
1849  }
1850  }
1851  }
1852  // find cross links
1853  encap_and_zeros_u8v(heap, bcnt[0] * bcnt[1]); // reuse heap as matrix
1854  for(i=0;i<nds->size;i++){
1855  wid = nds->buffer[i];
1856  w = ref_frgv(g->frgs, wid);
1857  idx = w->lnks[!w->rep_dir].idx;
1858  while(idx){
1859  f = ref_edgerefv(g->lrefs, idx);
1860  e = ref_lnkv(g->lnks, f->idx);
1861  idx = f->next;
1862  if(e->closed == WT_EDGE_CLOSED_HARD) continue;
1863  xid = f->flg? e->frg1 : e->frg2;
1864  if(xid == nid) continue;
1865  x = ref_frgv(g->frgs, xid);
1866  if(x->bt_visit != visit) continue;
1867  if(((w->bt_idx ^ x->bt_idx) & 0x01) == 0) continue;
1868  if(w->bt_idx & 0x01){
1869  if(x->bt_idx & 0x01){
1870  continue;
1871  } else {
1872  bidx = (x->bt_idx >> 1) * bcnt[1] + (w->bt_idx >> 1);
1873  }
1874  } else {
1875  if(x->bt_idx & 0x01){
1876  bidx = (w->bt_idx >> 1) * bcnt[1] + (x->bt_idx >> 1);
1877  } else {
1878  continue;
1879  }
1880  }
1881  eid = heap->buffer[bidx];
1882  if(eid == 0 || e->cov > g->lnks->buffer[eid].cov){
1883  heap->buffer[bidx] = eid = f->idx;
1884  }
1885  }
1886  }
1887  // find one-left to one-right links
1888  clear_u8v(nds); // will reuse nds to store bidx
1889  for(i=0;i<bcnt[0];i++){
1890  k = bcnt[1];
1891  for(j=0;j<bcnt[1];j++){
1892  if(heap->buffer[i * bcnt[1] + j]){
1893  if(k < bcnt[1]){
1894  k = bcnt[1];
1895  break;
1896  } else {
1897  k = j;
1898  }
1899  }
1900  }
1901  for(j=0;k<bcnt[1]&&j<bcnt[0];j++){
1902  if(j == i) continue;
1903  if(heap->buffer[j * bcnt[1] + k]){
1904  k = bcnt[1];
1905  break;
1906  }
1907  }
1908  if(k == bcnt[1]) continue;
1909  push_u8v(nds, i * bcnt[1] + k);
1910  }
1911  // detach repeats
1912  for(i=0;i<nds->size;i++){
1913  //bid[0] = nds->buffer[i] / bcnt[0];
1914  //bid[1] = nds->buffer[i] % bcnt[0];
1915  for(k=0;k<2;k++){
1916  idx = n->lnks[k].idx;
1917  bidx = k? (nds->buffer[i] % bcnt[0]) : (nds->buffer[i] / bcnt[0]);
1918  while(idx){
1919  f = ref_edgerefv(g->lrefs, idx);
1920  e = ref_lnkv(g->lnks, f->idx);
1921  idx = f->next;
1922  if(e->closed) continue;
1923  wid = f->flg? e->frg1 : e->frg2;
1924  w = ref_frgv(g->frgs, wid);
1925  if((w->bt_idx >> 1) == bidx){
1926  //cut_lnk_graph(g, e);
1927  cut_lnk_core_graph(g, e, WT_EDGE_CLOSED_HARD); // in case of loop cut and revive
1928  }
1929  }
1930  }
1931  }
1932  for(i=0;i<nds->size;i++){
1933  eid = heap->buffer[nds->buffer[i]];
1934  e = ref_lnkv(g->lnks, eid);
1935  revive_lnk_graph(g, e);
1936  }
1937  return nds->size;
1938 }

192  for(i=0;i<nd->regs.cnt;i++){
193  rg = ref_regv(g->regs, nd->regs.idx + i);

195  }

198  clear_subedgev(edges);
199  next_ref_subedgev(edges);
200  memset(&N, 0, sizeof(subnode_t));
201  N.cov = 1;
202  for(i=0;i<rds->size;i++){
203  rd = ref_readv(g->reads, rds->buffer[i]);
204  rg = NULL;
205  idx = rd->regs.idx;
206  while(idx){
207  rg = ref_regv(g->regs, idx);
208  idx = rg->read_link;
209  if(rg->closed) continue;
210  N.node = rg->node;
211  n = prepare_subnodehash(nodes, N, &exists);
212  if(exists){
213  n->cov ++;
214  } else {
215  *n = N;
216  }
217  }
218  }
219  // mask low cov nodes
220  reset_iter_subnodehash(nodes);
221  while((n = ref_iter_subnodehash(nodes))){
222  if(n->cov < g->min_node_cov) n->closed = 1;
223  }

232  idx = rg->read_link;
233  if(rg->closed) continue;
234  N.node = rg->node;
235  n2 = get_subnodehash(nodes, N);
236  k2 = rg->dir;
237  if(n2->closed) continue;
238  if(n1){
239  // link n1 to n2
240  edx = n1->edges[k1].idx;
241  while(edx){
242  e = ref_subedgev(edges, edx);
243  if(e->node == n2 && e->dir == k2){
244  e->cov ++;
245  break;
246  }
247  edx = e->next;
248  }
249  if(edx == 0){
250  edx = edges->size;
251  e = next_ref_subedgev(edges);
252  e->node = n2;
253  e->dir = k2;
254  e->cov = 1;
255  e->next = n1->edges[k1].idx;
256  n1->edges[k1].idx = edx;
257  n1->edges[k1].cnt ++;
258  }
259  // link rev n2 to rev n1
260  edx = n2->edges[!k2].idx;
261  while(edx){
262  e = ref_subedgev(edges, edx);
263  if(e->node == n1 && e->dir == !k1){
264  e->cov ++;
265  break;
266  }
267  edx = e->next;
268  }
269  if(edx == 0){
270  edx = edges->size;
271  e = next_ref_subedgev(edges);
272  e->node = n1;
273  e->dir = !k1;
274  e->cov = 1;
275  e->next = n2->edges[!k2].idx;
276  n2->edges[!k2].idx = edx;
277  n2->edges[!k2].cnt ++;
278  }
279  }
280  n1 = n2;
281  k1 = k2;
282  }
283  }
284  // find the nid node
285  N.node = nid;
286  n = get_subnodehash(nodes, N);
287  n->visit = 1;
288  // checking whether its out-edges collapse into one node
289  for(k=0;k<2;k++){
290  if(n->edges[k].cnt > 64) return 0;
291  if(n->edges[k].cnt < 2) continue;
292  idx = n->edges[k].idx;
293  cnt = 0;
294  while(idx){
295  e = ref_subedgev(edges, idx);
296  idx = e->next;
297  if(e->cov == 1) continue; // don't track low cov out-edges
298  cnt ++;
299  }
300  aim = 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFLLU >> (64 - cnt);
301  cnt = 0;
302  exists = 0;
303  if(k){
304  reset_iter_subnodehash(nodes);
305  while((n1 = ref_iter_subnodehash(nodes))){ n1->flag = 0; }
306  }
307  idx = n->edges[k].idx;
308  while(idx){
309  e = ref_subedgev(edges, idx);
310  idx = e->next;
311  if(e->cov == 1) continue; // don't track low cov out-edges
312  e->node->flag |= 1LLU << cnt;
313  cnt ++;
314  reset_iter_subnodehash(nodes);
315  while((n1 = ref_iter_subnodehash(nodes))){ n1->visit = 0; }
316  n->visit = 1;
317  clear_ptrrefv(stack);
318  push_ptrrefv(stack, (ptr_ref_t){offset_subnodehash(nodes, e->node), e->dir});
319  while(stack->size){
320  p = peer_ptrrefv(stack);
321  n1 = nodes->array + p->idx;
322  k1 = p->cnt;
323  stack->size --;
324  if(n1->flag == aim){ exists = 1; break; }
325  if(n1->visit) continue;
326  n1->visit = 1;
327  edx = n1->edges[k1].idx;
328  while(edx){
329  e = ref_subedgev(edges, edx);
330  edx = e->next;
331  if(e->node->visit) continue;
332  e->node->flag |= n1->flag;
333  push_ptrrefv(stack, (ptr_ref_t){offset_subnodehash(nodes, e->node), e->dir});
334  }
335  if(exists) break;
336  }
337  if(exists) break;
338  }
339  if(exists == 0) return 0;
340  }
341  return 1;
342 }

2014  f3 = ref_edgerefv(g->lrefs, u->val >> 1);
2015  e1 = ref_lnkv(g->lnks, f3->idx);
2016  k4 = f3->flg? !e1->dir1 : e1->dir2;
2017  if(k3 != k4) continue;
2018  v = ref_frgv(g->frgs, nid3);
2019  off1 = off2 = n->len + v->len;
2020  off1 += e1->off;
2021  off2 += e->off + e2->off + w->len;
2022  // check whether off1 and off2 diff too much
2023  if(num_diff(off1, off2) >= num_min(off1, off2)) continue;
2024  u->val |= 1;
2025  }
2026  }
2027  reset_iter_UUhash(hash);
2028  while((u = ref_iter_UUhash(hash))){
2029  if(u->val & 0x01){
2030  e = ref_lnkv(g->lnks, ref_edgerefv(g->lrefs, u->val >> 1)->idx);
2031  if(e->closed == WT_EDGE_CLOSED_NULL){
2032  cut_lnk_graph(g, e);
2033  ret ++;
2034  }
2035  }
2036  }
2037  }
2038  return ret;
2039 }

2699  n = ref_nodev(g->nodes, nid);
2700  if(n->closed) return 0;
2701  if(count_living_edges_graph(g, n, dir) < 2) return 0;
2702  clear_btv(bts);
2703  next_ref_btv(bts);
2704  bt = next_ref_btv(bts);
2705  bt->n = n;
2706  bt->e = NULL;
2707  bt->dir = dir;
2708  bt->step = 0;
2709  bt->bt = 0;
2710  bt->score = 0;
2711  bt->ending = 0;
2712  clear_u4v(heap);
2713  array_heap_push(heap->buffer, heap->size, heap->cap, u4i, bts->size - 1, num_cmpx(bts->buffer[a].step, bts->buffer[b].step, bts->buffer[b].score, bts->buffer[a].score));
2714  n->bt_visit = visit;
2715  n->bt_idx = bts->size - 1;
2716  tip = 0; tip_idx = WT_MAX_BTIDX;
2717  n_in = 1;
2718  while(heap->size && bts->size < WT_MAX_BTIDX){
2719  bidx = array_heap_pop(heap->buffer, heap->size, heap->cap, u4i, num_cmpx(bts->buffer[a].step, bts->buffer[b].step, bts->buffer[b].score, bts->buffer[a].score));
2720  encap_btv(bts, bts->buffer[bidx].n->edges[bts->buffer[bidx].dir].cnt);
2721  bt = ref_btv(bts, bidx);
2722  if(bt->step >= max_step){
2723  return 0;
2724  }
2725  lst = bts->size;
2726  idx = bt->n->edges[bt->dir].idx;
2727  while(idx){
2728  f = ref_edgerefv(g->erefs, idx);
2729  idx = f->next;
2730  e = g->edges->buffer + f->idx;
2731  if(e->closed) continue;
2732  tb = next_ref_btv(bts);
2733  tb->n = ref_nodev(g->nodes, f->flg? e->node1 : e->node2);
2734  //if(tb->n == bts->buffer[1].n) return 0;
2735  tb->e = e;
2736  tb->dir = f->flg? !e->dir1 : e->dir2;
2737  tb->step = bt->step + 1;
2738  tb->bt = bidx;
2739  tb->score = bt->score + e->cov;
2740  tb->ending = 0;
2741  }
2742  for(i=lst;i<bts->size;i++){
2743  tb = ref_btv(bts, i);
2744  if(tb->n->bt_visit != visit){
2745  tb->n->bt_visit = visit;
2746  tb->n->unvisit = count_living_edges_graph(g, tb->n, !tb->dir);
2747  n_in += tb->n->unvisit - 1;
2748  tb->n->bt_idx = i;
2749  if(count_living_edges_graph(g, tb->n, tb->dir)){
2750  array_heap_push(heap->buffer, heap->size, heap->cap, u4i, tb->n->bt_idx, num_cmpx(bts->buffer[a].step, bts->buffer[b].step, bts->buffer[b].score, bts->buffer[a].score));
2751  } else if(tip == 0){
2752  tip = 1;
2753  tip_idx = i;
2754  } else {
2755  return 0;
2756  }
2757  } else {
2758  tb->ending = tb->n->bt_idx;
2759  n_in --;
2760  }
2761  }
2762  if(n_in == 1){
2763  if(heap->size == 0 && tip == 1){
2764  return pop_bubble_backtrace_graph(g, bts, tip? tip_idx : heap->buffer[0]);
2765  } else if(heap->size == 1 && tip == 0){
2766  tip_idx = heap->buffer[0];
2767  tb = ref_btv(bts, heap->buffer[0]);
2768  idx = tb->n->edges[tb->dir].idx;
2769  while(idx){
2770  f = ref_edgerefv(g->erefs, idx);
2771  idx = f->next;
2772  e = g->edges->buffer + f->idx;
2773  if(e->closed) continue;
2774  m = ref_nodev(g->nodes, f->flg? e->node1 : e->node2);
2775  if(m->bt_visit == visit) continue;
2776  else tip ++;
2777  }
2778  if(tip == 0) return 0;
2779  return pop_bubble_backtrace_graph(g, bts, tip_idx);
2780  }
2781  }
2782  }
2783  return 0;
2784 }
